GLOSSARY OF TERMS
-----------------------------------------------------------------
* .eps FILE: Encapsulated PostScript file format

results.title: Embroidered Rope Trivet, Hot Pad, Kitchen Decor, Home Decor
results.description:
Embroidered rope trivets. Trivets are made of 3/16 inch diamond-braided polyester rope sewn in a coil fashion using a zig-zag sewing machine stitch. The back of the trivet looks almost as pretty as the front side.

Each trivet is embroidered with a different saying or object. This group of trivets contains the following three sayings:

Live, Laugh, Love
Bless This Home
Home Sweet Home

The fourth option for embroidery is an ornate cross.

Each completed trivet measures 8 inches in diameter. The rope is white. Embroidery colors are beige, light brown and grey.

Trivets are great for providing a decorative touch to your kitchen or dining room but can also be used on the counter or table top to protect them from warm pots, pans and serving dishes. 

Trivets and embroidery are durable and machine washable in warm or cold water. Lay flat to air dry.

The perfect wedding, newlywed shower or house warming gift.  Cooks will love to have these in their collection.

***Additional colors or variations may be requested through a custom order.

results.title: Repurposed jewelry, assemblage, short necklaces, Valentines jewelry
results.description:
Live well, laugh often and love much are great words to live by. They are stamped in this silver heart charm necklace that will make a great gift for a loved one or yourself! The 1"heart charm dangles from a 16" chain and is highlighted with an antique pearl bead. This classic necklace will wear well with any outfit.

Welcome to Recycled Finery!  I make jewelry made from recycled jewelry, coins, glass beads, vintage buttons, watch parts and charms.  My ever-growing collection of these materials comes from estate sales, church rummage sales, second-hand stores and family and friends’ collections they no longer need or want. I have fun putting these pieces together, whether they’re vintage, sentimental, elegant or just plain fun.  Sometimes the materials just speak for themselves.

I’ll be adding more pieces as I create them, so be sure to check back often. My jewelry makes great gifts as they are unique and reasonably priced. Often at holiday craft shows, shoppers end up buying multiple pieces, keeping one and gifting another.  I’ll be curious to hear what you think. Thanks for shopping!
